                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-215-victim1549 t18310407-215-viclabel1158"></join>. We have known the prisoner a year and a half - he lodged with us twice; the last time for four months; he owed us nearly thirty pounds - he went out in February last to go to his attorney, as he said; I missed these things while he was with us.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. I believe he is a Portuguese, who was obliged to fly from Don Miguel? A. Yes; he paid us honestly as long as he had money; and being distressed, I believe my husband at times gave him leave to pledge a few things, and he has redeemed them - he might have intended to redeem these.</p>
